(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/pca-connector-ad/latest/APIReference/API_CreateTemplate.html).


=head2 ConnectorArn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) that was returned when you called
CreateConnector
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/pca-connector-ad/latest/APIReference/API_CreateConnector.html).


=head2 CreatedAt => Str

The date and time that the template was created.


=head2 Definition => L<Paws::PcaConnectorAd::TemplateDefinition>

Template configuration to define the information included in
certificates. Define certificate validity and renewal periods,
certificate request handling and enrollment options, key usage
extensions, application policies, and cryptography settings.


=head2 Name => Str

Name of the templates. Template names must be unique.


=head2 ObjectIdentifier => Str

Object identifier of a template.


=head2 PolicySchema => Int

The template schema version. Template schema versions can be v2, v3, or
v4. The template configuration options change based on the template
schema version.


=head2 Revision => L<Paws::PcaConnectorAd::TemplateRevision>

The version of the template. Template updates will increment the minor
revision. Re-enrolling all certificate holders will increment the major
revision.


=head2 Status => Str

Status of the template. Status can be creating, active, deleting, or
failed.


